Name: Jagajaga
Description:
The Division of Jagajaga consists of:

  • Banyule City Council, and
  • part of the Nillumbik Shire Council.
ProductsAndIndustry: Commercial and light industrial area which includes construction, and retail trade.
NameDerivation: Named in honour of the three principal Aboriginal elders who signed a treaty with John Batman in 1835 which intended to give the white settlers 500,000 acres of land at the north-west end of Port Phillip Bay and 100,000 acres around Geelong.
DemographicRating: Inner Metropolitan - situated in capital cities and consisting of well-established built-up suburbs.
